This paper deals with the logical modeling of statistical probabilities and degrees of belief, which are central topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of cross entropy minimization, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents a logical framework for default reasoning, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO).
